# **Cipher Squad ‚Äî Extended Game Design Document (GDD)**

## **1\. High-Level Concept**

**Cipher Squad** is a daily, collaborative logic puzzle game built natively for Telegram. Entire Telegram groups (‚ÄúSquads‚Äù) cooperate **asynchronously** to solve a shared Daily Vault faster than rival squads.

The game is explicitly designed to survive real-world Telegram behavior: solo testers, AFK users, unreliable connectivity, race conditions, and uneven contribution.

**Design Pillar:** *Smart together beats smart alone ‚Äî enforced by systems, not trust.*

---

## **2\. Strategic Positioning**

### **Why This Game Exists**

* Tap-to-earn fatigue has reduced long-term retention  
* Telegram‚Äôs audience values intelligence signaling and social status  
* Group chats provide zero-cost viral distribution

Cipher Squad sits at the intersection of:

* Daily habit games (Wordle, Daily Cipher)  
* Group-based competition  
* Skill-first, non-grind gameplay

---

## **3\. Target Audience**

* Tech-savvy Telegram users  
* Crypto, dev, puzzle, analytics communities  
* Active Telegram groups (10‚Äì500 members)

**Secondary Audience:** Solo users testing the bot before adding it to a group

---

## **4\. Core Design Pillars**

1. **Async by Default**  
   No mechanic may require real-time coordination.  
2. **Grief-Resistant by Design**  
   Systems assume AFK, selfish, or unreliable players.  
3. **Forced Collaboration**  
   A full Daily Vault cannot be efficiently completed by a single player.  
4. **Prove Fun Before Social Ask**  
   Solo users must experience a win before being asked to invite others.  
5. **Bridge, Don‚Äôt Block**  
   If social coordination is unavailable, the system must offer a fallback path.  
6. **No Pay-to-Win**  
   Monetization may reduce friction or add status, never guarantee victory.

---

## **5\. Game Modes**

### **5.1 Bootcamp Vault (Solo Onboarding)**

**Purpose:** Convert solo testers into engaged players.

* Triggered when a user opens the app outside of a group context  
* Mini Vault with **2√ó2 tiles**, very low difficulty  
* Fully solo-solvable

**Win State:**

‚ÄúYou crushed the Bootcamp\! Ready for the real challenge?‚Äù

After completion, the user is offered two explicit paths:

* **Add Bot to a Group** (primary CTA)  
* **Join a Public Squad** (Mercenary Mode)

Bootcamp Vault is **one-time only**, has no leaderboard, and no monetization.

---

### **5.2 Mercenary Squads (Public / Soft Squads)**

**Purpose:** Bridge solo users into the core Daily Vault loop without requiring immediate social coordination.

* Available only after Bootcamp completion  
* Server auto-assigns solo users into temporary public squads (e.g., `Mercs_#492`)  
* Mercenary Squads can play the Daily Vault normally

**Constraints:**

* No persistent squad identity  
* No cosmetics or seasons  
* No long-term progression

Players may later migrate to a private Telegram group Squad at any time.

---

### **5.3 Daily Vault (Core Mode)**

* Opens daily at UTC 00:00  
* Identical for all Squads (private and mercenary)  
* Completion time determines leaderboard rank

---

## **6\. Core Loop (Daily Vault)**

1. Daily Vault opens  
2. Squad sees a **Mosaic Grid** (initially 3√ó3 tiles)  
3. Each tile is an **independent logic puzzle**  
4. Squad members:  
   * Open the Mini App from the group or squad  
   * Claim an available tile  
   * Attempt to solve it under a temporary lock  
5. Solved tiles flip permanently, revealing part of a larger image  
6. When all tiles are solved:  
   * Vault completion time is recorded  
   * Squad is ranked globally

---

## **7\. Mosaic & Puzzle Design**

### **7.1 Mosaic Structure**

* Vault consists of N independent tiles (V1: 9\)  
* Each tile contains a self-contained logic puzzle (e.g., 10√ó10 Nonogram)  
* Tiles are logically independent but visually cohesive

When all tiles are solved, they assemble into a single pixel-art image.

---

### **7.2 Puzzle Generation Pipeline (Hard Constraints)**

**Generation Steps:**

1. AI generates a **master pixel-art image** (e.g., 30√ó30)  
2. Image is sliced into N tiles (e.g., nine 10√ó10 grids)  
3. Each tile is converted into a logic puzzle  
4. A deterministic validator evaluates **each tile**

**Entropy & Quality Rules (Mandatory):**

* Tile fill rate must be between **30% and 70%**  
* Tile must not be fully empty or fully filled  
* Tile must require at least **N logical steps** to solve  
* Tile must have a **unique valid solution**

**Failure Rule:**

If **any** tile fails validation, the **entire master image is rejected** and regenerated.

No partial regeneration is allowed.

---

## **8\. Tile Claiming, Locks & Draft Recovery**

### **8.1 Soft-Lock System**

* Claiming a tile grants a **temporary lock** (default: 5 minutes)  
* Any meaningful interaction refreshes the timer  
* If the timer expires:  
  * Tile becomes claimable by others  
  * Server-side progress is cleared

---

### **8.2 Client-Side Draft Recovery (UX Protection)**

* Tile draft state is cached in client `localStorage`  
* If the same user reclaims the same tile **before another user completes it**:  
  * Cached draft is restored  
* If another user completes the tile:  
  * Cached draft is discarded

This preserves fairness while preventing rage-quits caused by connectivity loss.

---

## **9\. Contribution Enforcement (Anti-Carry)**

### **Design Goal**

Prevent a single expert from solving the entire Vault while others spectate.

### **V1 Mechanic: Soft Contribution Friction**

* Each player can efficiently solve a limited number of tiles per Vault  
* Beyond the threshold:  
  * Cooldowns or delays are applied  
  * UI messaging encourages recruiting another member

Hard caps are explicitly out of scope for V1.

---

## **10\. Social & Viral Mechanics**

### **Help Signal (Mandatory)**

Inside an active tile, players may tap **‚ÄúAsk Squad for Help‚Äù**.

This posts a message into the Telegram group or squad chat:

‚ÄúüÜò @User is stuck on Tile 4 (80% complete)\! Click here to take over.‚Äù

This mechanic:

* Re-engages dormant users  
* Creates contextual deep links  
* Reinforces the Squad loop

---

## **11\. Leaderboards**

* Ranked by Vault completion time  
* Only completed Squads appear  
* Includes private Squads and Mercenary Squads

---

## **12\. Monetization (V1 Scope)**

### **Telegram Stars**

Allowed purchases:

* **Extend Tile Lock** (individual friction reduction)  
* **Retry Failed Tile**  
* **Reveal Hint** (non-solving)  
* **Cosmetic Squad Badge** (status signaling, private squads only)

### **Explicitly Deferred**

* Auto-complete / panic buttons  
* Squad-wide buffs (e.g., ‚ÄúSquad Coffee‚Äù)

---

## **13\. Technical Stack (Confirmed)**

### **Frontend**

* Telegram Mini App  
* React \+ Vite  
* Lightweight 2D rendering

### **Backend**

* Cloudflare Workers (BFF)  
* REST JSON APIs

### **Database**

* Cloudflare D1 (SQLite)  
* One database per game

**Core Tables (V1):**

* squads  
* daily\_vaults  
* tiles  
* tile\_locks  
* tile\_completions  
* member\_stats

### **Data Integrity Rules**

* Tile completion uses **transactional writes**  
* Only the first valid completion succeeds  
* Subsequent attempts receive `ALREADY_SOLVED`

**UX Requirement:**

Losing the race must trigger a positive reinforcement animation, not an error state.
